Generate shell completion scripts for fotingo.

Completions allow you to press <TAB> to autocomplete commands, flags, and arguments.

Supported shells:
  bash   - Bash completion script
  zsh    - Zsh completion script
  fish   - Fish completion script
  powershell - PowerShell completion script

Installation Instructions:

  Bash (Linux):
    # Add to your ~/.bashrc:
    source <(fotingo completion bash)

    # Or install system-wide:
    fotingo completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/fotingo

  Bash (macOS with Homebrew):
    # First, ensure bash-completion is installed:
    brew install bash-completion

    # Add to your ~/.bash_profile:
    source <(fotingo completion bash)

  Zsh:
    # Add to your ~/.zshrc (before compinit):
    source <(fotingo completion zsh)

    # Or generate a file in your fpath:
    fotingo completion zsh > "${fpath[1]}/_fotingo"

    # You may need to run this once for new completions:
    rm -f ~/.zcompdump; compinit

  Fish:
    # Add to your Fish config:
    fotingo completion fish | source

    # Or generate a file:
    fotingo completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/fotingo.fish

  PowerShell:
    # Add to your PowerShell profile:
    fotingo completion powershell | Out-String | Invoke-Expression

Examples:
  # Generate and source bash completions inline
  source <(fotingo completion bash)

  # Generate zsh completions to a file
  fotingo completion zsh > /usr/local/share/zsh/site-functions/_fotingo

  # Test completion output
  fotingo completion bash | head -20

Usage:
  fotingo completion [shell]

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for completion

Global Flags:
  -b, --branch string   Base branch override (default: auto-detect)
      --debug           Show diagnostic output (includes verbose)
      --json            Output results as JSON
      --no-color        Disable colored output
      --quiet           Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose         Show step-level progress output
  -y, --yes             Accept defaults without prompting
